  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Post-Ebola Surveillance Systems in the N&apos;Z&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; Region in Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project&#x2019;s activities are in line with the priorities of the Guinean government&#x2019;s plan to strengthen post Ebola surveillance systems in N&#x2019;Z&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; region and the National Action Plan for Health Security (NAPHS- ANSS) in Guinea. The activities will be closely coordinated with the NAPHS, which aims to bring together actors from the Government, IOM, and other partners, ensuring that activities are in line with the overall strategy of the government based on its needs. The project objective is to strengthen health security efforts as aligned to the government&#x2019;s current strategy and will improve epidemic response capacities in high-risk local districts in N&#x2019;Z&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; region in Guinea.</narrative>
  </description>
